-- IFC to Provide $170 Million to First City Bank of Nigeria, ThisDay Reports
-- Vincent Nwanma
-- 2010-07-22T09:19:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/ifc-to-provide-170-million-to-first-city-bank-of-nigeria-thisday-reports.html

          
          
             International Finance Corp., the
World Bank unit that lends to companies, will provide $170
million to Nigeriaâ€™s  First City Monument Bank Plc ,  ThisDay 
reported today, citing Chief Executive Officer  Ladi Balogun .  
 The IFC will invest $60 million as equity while $110
million will be long-term debt maturing in seven years at an
interest rate of about 4.5 percent a year, the Lagos-based
newspaper said. Shareholders of the bank approved the investment
plan, according to ThisDay.  
